# React Native — UI Performance

Apply when changing screens, lists, or animated UI. Core naming and module rules live in `expo-project.mdc`.

## Render & lists

- Keep expensive work out of render; move to effects, worklets, or plain utilities.
- **FlatList / SectionList:** tune `removeClippedSubviews`, `maxToRenderPerBatch`, `windowSize`; use `getItemLayout` when row height is fixed.
- Avoid anonymous inline functions as list `renderItem` when they force avoidable child re-renders (compiler helps, but stable handlers still matter for heavy rows).

## Styling & assets

- Prefer `StyleSheet.create()` for non-trivial styles (co-located in the same file is fine; separate `.styles.ts` only when a screen file grows large).
- Consider screen size and safe areas; use `react-native-safe-area-context` on edge-to-edge layouts.
- Use RN-friendly image libraries (e.g. `expo-image`) for large or remote assets — not unoptimized `<Image>` hot paths.

## Runtime

- Respect RN threading: gesture and animation on UI thread (Reanimated worklets); avoid blocking the JS thread during scroll and transitions.
- Navigation: React Navigation patterns for stacks, tabs, and deep links.
